\f0\i\b\fs28 \cf2 \ul \ulc2 Lasagna della nonna Ingrid
\f1\i0 \ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \
Every Italian family has its own version of this popular comforting dish - and this one is no exception. Even 
\f3\i king Ferdinand II 
\f2\i0 was said to like it so much that he earned the nickname \'93
\f3\i the Lasagna King!\'94
\f2\i0 \
\
The origins of lasagna go back to ancient Rome, where a dish called 
\f3\i laganum
\f2\i0  consisted of a thin layer of wheat dough baked with a meat topping
\f3\i . 
\f2\i0 Its evolution into a tomato-based dish was developed much later in 19th-century Naples. In 1881, recipes resembling modern lasagna began to appear in Neapolitan cuisine. \
\
In the 20th century, the version known as 
\f0\i\b lasagne Verdi alla bolognese
\f2\i0\b0  was formalized by the 
\f3\i Accademia Italiana della Cucina 
\f2\i0 and registered in the 
\f3\i Chamber of Commerce of Felsina (the original Etruscan name of Bologna)
\f2\i0 . For this reason the dish is commonly associated with Bologna rather than Naples, where its earlier forms originated.\
\
The two traditions differ significantly: 
\f3\i Neapolitan lasagna 
\f2\i0 uses white pasta, Neapolitan rag\'f9, meatballs, ricotta, Provola  and Pecorino cheeses, while
\f3\i  Bolognese lasagna 
\f2\i0 uses green pasta, bolognese rag\'f9, b\'e9chamel and Parmigiano Reggiano.\
\
Although my family comes from the south of Italy 
\f3\i (Puglia), 
\f2\i0 my favorite version is the Bolognese one. For practicality, I use white, oven-ready pasta but I also include instructions for homemade pasta if you wish to prepare the quintessential lasagna for a special occasion.\
\
Yield: 6 servings\
Prep Time: 1 hour\
Cook time: 2 \'bd hours\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf2 Ingredients\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Meat sauce
\f2\b0 \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}1 large onion, chopped\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}2 garlic cloves, peeled and finely chopped\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}1/4 cup finely chopped bacon \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}1 carrot (chopped)\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}1 celery stick (chopped)\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}500 g ground meat (half pork/veal, half beef)\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}1 cup strong red wine\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}1200 g canned crushed tomatoes\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}1 tsp dried oregano
\fs36 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b\fs28 \cf2 \
{\listtext	\'95	}Bechamel\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}6 Tbsp butter (80 g)\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}6 Tbsp all-purpose white flour (60g)\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}3 cups whole milk\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}3 cups beef broth\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}1/2 cup grated 
\f3\i Parmigiano Reggiano
\f2\i0 \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}1/2 tsp nutmeg (preferably freshly grated)\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Salt and pepper to taste\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf2 \
\ls4\ilvl0\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl1
\f1\b \cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Other ingredients\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b0 \cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}700 g mozzarella\
\ls4\ilvl0{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}basil leaves cut into strips\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}3 Tbsp olive oil\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}1 cup grated 
\f3\i Parmigiano Reggiano\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f2\i0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}1 cup frozen peas (optional)\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
